articles.title: Brian Harman hunts first major but McIlroy not ruling himself out of Open - The Guardian
articles.description: The American Brian Harman finished day two on 10 under, with his nearest challenger Tommy Fleetwood five back, as Rory McIlroy said: ‘We’ll see what the weekend holds’
articles.content: Thirty-six holes down, a five-shot lead. The hunter has become the hunted. Ominously for Brian Harman, in the quintet of mainstream events where he has held any form of advantage at the halfway point… [+9768 chars]
